# Documentation Rules

## Pre-Change Checklist
- [ ] Review all relevant rules before making any changes
- [ ] Check if changes affect:
  - Routes
  - Types
  - Middleware
  - Auth requirements
- [ ] Update OpenAPI spec if any of the above are modified
- [ ] Update Postman collection if API changes
- [ ] Document all changes in code

## OpenAPI Documentation
- [ ] Update `openapi.yml` when adding/modifying routes
- [ ] Keep OpenAPI spec in sync with:
  - Endpoint definitions
  - Input/output types
  - Auth requirements
- [ ] Update Postman collection when API changes

## Code Documentation
- [ ] Add descriptive comments to all functions
- [ ] Document:
  - Purpose
  - Parameters
  - Return values
  - Side effects/assumptions

## Example Function Documentation
```go
// GetUser handles the retrieval of a user by ID.
// Params:
// - c: the Gin context containing request and response
// Returns a JSON object with the user data, or an error response.
func (h *UserHandler) GetUser(c *gin.Context) { ... }
```

## Best Practices
- [ ] Use clear, consistent language
- [ ] Make code easy to understand and extend
- [ ] Keep documentation up to date

